Page 6: Flange Numbering Diagram

Flange Identification System

Critical reference for identifying and matching flange plates during assembly. Each flange is numbered for proper component matching.

Flange No. 1

Top platform level connection points. Used for upper structure assembly and decorative ball mounting.

Flange No. 2

Upper mid-level connections. Primary structural support flanges for platform stability.

Flange No. 3

Lower mid-level connections. Support lower platform and intermediate structural elements.

Flange No. 4

Ground level foundation flanges. Critical for base stability and proper load distribution.

Flange Installation Guidelines

  • Match flange numbers between mating components
  • Ensure bolt holes align properly before tightening
  • Use lock washers on all flange connections
  • Tighten bolts in star pattern for even pressure distribution
  • Verify flange alignment with level before final tightening
  • Reference installation photos for proper orientation
  • Apply appropriate thread-locking compound where specified
